KeyVaultClient

Initializes a new instance of the KeyVaultClient class.

Constructor

new KeyVaultClient(credentials, optionsopt)

Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
credentials credentials

Credentials needed for the client to connect to Azure.
options object <optional>

The parameter options

Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
filters Array <optional>

Filters to be added to the request pipeline
requestOptions object <optional>

Options for the underlying request object
Options doc
noRetryPolicy boolean <optional>

If set to true, turn off default retry policy
apiVersion string <optional>

Client Api Version.
acceptLanguage string <optional>

Gets or sets the preferred language for the response.
longRunningOperationRetryTimeout number <optional>

Gets or sets the retry timeout in seconds for Long Running Operations. Default value is 30.
generateClientRequestId boolean <optional>

When set to true a unique x-ms-client-request-id value is generated and included in each request. Default is true.

createKey(vaultBaseUrl, keyName, kty, optionsopt, optionalCallbackopt) → {function|Promise}

Creates a new key, stores it, then returns key parameters and attributes to
the client. The create key operation can be used to create any key type in
Azure Key Vault. If the named key already exists, Azure Key Vault creates a
new version of the key. Authorization: Requires the keys/create permission.

Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
vaultBaseUrl string

The vault name, for example
https://myvault.vault.azure.net.
keyName string

The name for the new key. The system will generate
the version name for the new key.
kty string

The type of key to create. For valid key types, see
JsonWebKeyType. Supported JsonWebKey key types (kty) for Elliptic Curve,
RSA, HSM, Octet. Possible values include: 'EC', 'RSA', 'RSA-HSM', 'oct'
options object <optional>

Optional Parameters.

Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
keySize number <optional>

The key size in bytes. For example, 1024
or 2048.
keyOps array <optional>
keyAttributes object <optional>
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
enabled boolean <optional>

Determines whether the
object is enabled.
notBefore date <optional>

Not before date in UTC.
expires date <optional>

Expiry date in UTC.
tags object <optional>

Application specific metadata in the form of
key-value pairs.
customHeaders object <optional>

Headers that will be added to the
request
optionalCallback function <optional>

The optional callback.
Source:
  • keyVaultClient.js, line 8627
Returns:

If a callback was passed as the last parameter
then it returns the callback else returns a Promise.

{Promise} A promise is returned

Type
function | Promise

createKeyWithHttpOperationResponse(vaultBaseUrl, keyName, keyType, optionsopt) → {Promise}

Creates a new key, stores it, then returns key parameters and attributes to
the client. The create key operation can be used to create any key type in
Azure Key Vault. If the named key already exists, Azure Key Vault creates a
new version of the key. Authorization: Requires the keys/create permission.

Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
vaultBaseUrl string

The vault name, for example
https://myvault.vault.azure.net.
keyName string

The name for the new key. The system will generate
the version name for the new key.
keyType string

The type of key to create. For valid key types, see
JsonWebKeyType. Supported JsonWebKey key types (kty) for Elliptic Curve,
RSA, HSM, Octet. Possible values include: 'EC', 'RSA', 'RSA-HSM', 'oct'
options object <optional>

Optional Parameters.

Properties
Name Type Attributes Description

The key size in bytes. For example, 1024
or 2048.

Properties
Name Type Attributes Description

Determines whether the

importKey(vaultBaseUrl, keyName, key, optionsopt, optionalCallbackopt) → {function|Promise}

Imports an externally created key, stores it, and returns key parameters and
attributes to the client. The import key operation may be used to import any
key type into an Azure Key Vault. If the named key already exists, Azure Key
Vault creates a new version of the key. Authorization: requires the
keys/import permission.

Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
vaultBaseUrl string

The vault name, for example
https://myvault.vault.azure.net.
keyName string

Name for the imported key.
key object

The Json web key

Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
kid string <optional>

Key identifier.
kty string <optional>

Supported JsonWebKey key types (kty) for Elliptic
Curve, RSA, HSM, Octet. Kty is usually set to RSA. Possible values include:
'EC', 'RSA', 'RSA-HSM', 'oct'
keyOps array <optional>
n buffer <optional>

RSA modulus.
e buffer <optional>

RSA public exponent.
d buffer <optional>

RSA private exponent.
dp buffer <optional>

RSA private key parameter.
dq buffer <optional>

RSA private key parameter.
qi buffer <optional>

RSA private key parameter.
p buffer <optional>

RSA secret prime.
q buffer <optional>

RSA secret prime, with p < q.
k buffer <optional>

Symmetric key.
t buffer <optional>

HSM Token, used with 'Bring Your Own Key'.
options object <optional>

Optional Parameters.

Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
hsm boolean <optional>

Whether to import as a hardware key (HSM) or
software key.
keyAttributes object <optional>

The key management attributes.

Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
enabled boolean <optional>

Determines whether the
object is enabled.
notBefore date <optional>

Not before date in UTC.
expires date <optional>

Expiry date in UTC.
tags object <optional>

Application specific metadata in the form of
key-value pairs.
customHeaders object <optional>

Headers that will be added to the
request
optionalCallback function <optional>

The optional callback.
Source:
  • keyVaultClient.js, line 8813

updateKey(keyIdentifier, optionsopt, optionalCallbackopt) → {function|Promise}

The update key operation changes specified attributes of a stored key and
can be applied to any key type and key version stored in Azure Key Vault.
The cryptographic material of a key itself cannot be changed. In order to
perform this operation, the key must already exist in the Key Vault.
Authorization: requires the keys/update permission.

Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
keyIdentifier string

The key identifier. It may or may not contain a version path.
If a version is not provided, the latest key version is used.
options object <optional>

Optional Parameters.

Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
keyOps array <optional>

Json web key operations. For more
information on possible key operations, see JsonWebKeyOperation.
keyAttributes object <optional>

object is enabled

Not before date in UTC

Expiry date in UTC

createKey(vaultBaseUrl, keyName, kty, optionsopt, optionalCallbackopt) → {function|Promise}

Creates a new key, stores it, then returns key parameters and attributes to
the client. The create key operation can be used to create any key type in
Azure Key Vault. If the named key already exists, Azure Key Vault creates a
new version of the key. Authorization: Requires the keys/create permission.

Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
vaultBaseUrl string

The vault name, for example
https://myvault.vault.azure.net.
keyName string

The name for the new key. The system will generate
the version name for the new key.
kty string

The type of key to create. For valid key types, see
JsonWebKeyType. Supported JsonWebKey key types (kty) for Elliptic Curve,
RSA, HSM, Octet. Possible values include: 'EC', 'RSA', 'RSA-HSM', 'oct'

importKey(vaultBaseUrl, keyName, key, optionsopt, optionalCallbackopt) → {function|Promise}

Imports an externally created key, stores it, and returns key parameters and
attributes to the client. The import key operation may be used to import any
key type into an Azure Key Vault. If the named key already exists, Azure Key
Vault creates a new version of the key. Authorization: requires the
keys/import permission.

Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
vaultBaseUrl string

The vault name, for example
https://myvault.vault.azure.net.
keyName string

Name for the imported key.
key object

The Json web key

Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
kid string <optional>

Key identifier.
kty string <optional>

Supported JsonWebKey key types (kty) for Elliptic
Curve, RSA, HSM, Octet. Kty is usually set to RSA. Possible values include:
'EC', 'RSA', 'RSA-HSM', 'oct'
keyOps array <optional>
n buffer <optional>

RSA modulus.
e buffer <optional>

RSA public exponent.
d buffer <optional>

RSA private exponent.
dp buffer <optional>

RSA private key parameter.
dq buffer <optional>

RSA private key parameter.
qi buffer <optional>

RSA private key parameter.
p buffer <optional>

RSA secret prime.
q buffer <optional>

RSA secret prime, with p < q.
k buffer <optional>

Symmetric key.
t buffer <optional>

HSM Token, used with 'Bring Your Own Key'.
options object <optional>

Optional Parameters.

Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
hsm boolean <optional>

Whether to import as a hardware key (HSM) or
software key.
keyAttributes object <optional>

The key management attributes.

Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
enabled boolean <optional>

Determines whether the
object is enabled.
notBefore date <optional>

Not before date in UTC.
expires date <optional>

Expiry date in UTC.
tags object <optional>

Application specific metadata in the form of
key-value pairs.
customHeaders object <optional>

Headers that will be added to the
request
optionalCallback function <optional>

The optional callback.
Source:
  • keyVaultClient.js, line 8813

updateKey(keyIdentifier, optionsopt, optionalCallbackopt) → {function|Promise}

The update key operation changes specified attributes of a stored key and
can be applied to any key type and key version stored in Azure Key Vault.
The cryptographic material of a key itself cannot be changed. In order to
perform this operation, the key must already exist in the Key Vault.
Authorization: requires the keys/update permission.

Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
keyIdentifier string

The key identifier. It may or may not contain a version path.
If a version is not provided, the latest key version is used.
options object <optional>

Optional Parameters.

Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
keyOps array <optional>

Json web key operations. For more
information on possible key operations, see JsonWebKeyOperation.
keyAttributes object <optional>
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
enabled boolean <optional>

Determines whether the
object is enabled
notBefore date <optional>

Not before date in UTC
expires date <optional>

Expiry date in UTC
tags object <optional>

Application-specific metadata in the form of
key-value pairs
customHeaders object <optional>

Headers that will be added to the
request

The optional callback.
